{"id":6813,"date":"2017-10-04T09:19:49","date_gmt":"2017-10-04T16:19:49","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=6813"},"modified":"2017-10-04T09:19:49","modified_gmt":"2017-10-04T16:19:49","slug":"wards-ferry-trail","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/10\/04\/wards-ferry-trail\/","title":{"rendered":"WARD\u2019S FERRY TRAIL"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>An 8 km riverside trail following the Kootenay River from Glade north to Rover Creek Road across the river from South Slocan.<\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> easy B1<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Elevation gained:<\/strong> 200m (Glade to S Slocan)<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 8km<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Time: <\/strong>3 hours<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> Year-round<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82F\/5 Castlegar<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> Access from Glade: Head North on Hwy 3A towards Nelson. Turn right after lumber yard at Glade Ferry sign. Cross the Kootenay River on the Glade Ferry. Take the first left on Glade Road. When this road turns to gravel (1.7km), keep to your left and continue on for 0.5km<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"> Access from South Slocan: Head east on Hwy 3A towards Nelson. Exit right on Blewett Road just passed S. Slocan Village Road on the left. Travel on Blewett Road for 3.6km crossing the Kootenay River. Turn right on Rover Creek Forest Service Road just after the canal bridge. Follow for 1.5km and park by the clearing on the right, this is the trailhead.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong> Most of this trail follows the shore of the Kootenay River, there are many opportunities to stop and watch Mother Nature at work. There are some challenging sections so wear good shoes.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Dog and bike friendly. Facilities none. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"> This trail is maintained by the Nelson and Area Trails Society.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>An 8 km riverside trail following the Kootenay River from Glade north to Rover Creek Road across the river from South Slocan. Difficulty: easy B1 Elevation gained: 200m (Glade to S Slocan) Distance: 8km Time: 3 hours Season: Year-round Map: &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/10\/04\/wards-ferry-trail\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[1],"tags